data.title: Inszone Insurance
data.meta_description: Meet the Inszone Insurance Team. You can learn more about each member of our team and their experience by clicking on their photo.
data.text:
Chris Walters is a Principal Owner and CEO of Inszone Insurance Services. A charismatic leader and adept strategist, Chris Walters has built a reputation as a critical thinker, problem solver, and accomplished entrepreneur. As the Principal Owner and CEO of Inszone Insurance Services, Chris’s visionary leadership has been instrumental in transforming a fledgling agency into a multi-state powerhouse, now boasting numerous offices and over 400 employees.

A graduate of Humboldt State University with a degree in Business Administration, Chris also carries the designation of Commercial Lines Coverage Specialist. Leveraging his educational background and an innate entrepreneurial spirit, he has successfully orchestrated the growth of Inszone, applying his knowledge and experience in every aspect of the business.

With over 20 years of experience in the insurance industry, Chris is a seasoned sales manager. His acumen in building high-performing sales teams is not just notable but integral to the success and growth of Inszone. Over the years, Chris has assisted thousands of families and businesses in safeguarding their investments, laying the foundation for enduring relationships rooted in trust and mutual respect.

Chris’s leadership style is defined by his calm demeanor, his ability to view the bigger picture, and his unwavering focus on long-term strategies. He leads with purpose and is driven by facts, using his problem-solving skills to navigate the complexities of the insurance industry.

Outside of his professional accomplishments, Chris is a devoted husband and proud father of two beautiful girls. He finds joy in golfing, traveling, and hosting, and is always ready to roll up his sleeves to accomplish both business and personal goals. Grounded and personable, Chris seamlessly blends his entrepreneurial drive with his roles as a leader, family man, and community member.

Jit Hazra is the CFO at Inszone Insurance Services. Joining the company in 2022, Jit brings over 20 years of financial executive experience in the insurance industry. He served as VP, Head of North American Field Finance for The Hanover Insurance Company from 2012 until 2017, where he helped optimize profitability and growth. Most recently he served as CFO for GGBUS (Gallagher Global Brokerage US) since 2017. A graduate of Michigan State University, Jit holds a bachelor’s in Finance and Business Management. He also earned an MBA from the Booth School of Business at the University of Chicago. In his current role at Inszone he oversees all aspects of Finance & Accounting for the organization, driving the business towards articulating & achieving all financial goals.

On his time off, Jit enjoy spending quality time with his family, cooking, vacationing, listening to classis LPs, and watching movies.

Pat Grignon is the Chief Revenue Officer (CRO) at Inszone Insurance Services. Pat has over 15 years of experience as an insurance executive and licensed insurance agent. He holds a bachelor’s degree in Business Administration with a minor in Economics and maintains a designation as a Commercial Lines Coverage Specialist (CLCS). In his previous role at Inszone, Pat oversaw all aspects of the sales division, working diligently to recruit and train every staff member to maximize their potential while becoming more organized and providing the best possible customer experience. Now as CRO, all aspects of sales and service report to Mr. Grignon, and he is laser focused on organic growth, helping the company to achieve it’s goals.

An avid golfer, proud father and husband, and an impeccable man of leisure, Pat is an integral part of the Inszone Team.

Matt Rieck is the Chief Human Resources Officer at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in June 2023. Matt holds an MBA in Organizational Development from Webster University and a Bachelor’s Degree in Psychology from Chapman University, providing him with a strong foundation for his role. With over 20 years of professional experience in Human Resources, Matt has held leadership positions at several renowned companies, successfully implementing innovative HR practices in the insurance industry and aligning them with business objectives.

Throughout his career, Matt has demonstrated his ability to empower employees and foster a positive work culture, resulting in high levels of employee satisfaction, increased productivity, and improved overall organizational performance. His passion for cultivating a supportive and engaging work environment has been a driving force behind his successful track record. With his expertise and dedication, Matt continues to bring his wealth of knowledge and proven strategies to Inszone Insurance Services, further enhancing the company’s HR practices and contributing to its success.

Matt is a father of three children and enjoys working out, playing with his English Bulldogs, and having movie nights with his family.

Kathleen Kozlowski is the VP of Carrier Relations at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in May 2023. She began her career as an underwriter and quickly gained expertise in the intricacies of the insurance industry which led to her progression through various account management roles at leading insurance brokerages. With a remarkable track record spanning over three decades in the insurance sector, Kathleen has held strategic positions and showcased her exceptional skills in building relationships. Kathleen’s contributions have been instrumental in serving high-value clients, establishing her reputation as a trusted business relationship manager for major players in the financial services sector, including JP Morgan and Wells Fargo.

At the core of Kathleen’s business approach is an unwavering commitment to cultivating lasting relationships. She emphasizes the importance of getting to know people on a personal level and takes great pride in doing so. With her remarkable interpersonal skills and natural ability to foster connections, Kathleen is an invaluable asset in establishing and enriching partnerships with carrier business partners.

Amy Hieatt is an Executive VP – North American Health Care Practice Leader at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in September 2023. In her role, Amy is responsible for overseeing the strategic direction and day-to-day operations of Inszone’s national healthcare liability vertical, with a strong emphasis on maintaining a customer-centric approach.

Over the past 20+ years, Amy has dedicated her career to the property and casualty insurance sector, focusing extensively on the Medical Professional Liability and Professional Liability sectors. Prior to her role at Inszone, she served as the Managing Director at Connected Risk Solutions (formerly ABRisk Solutions), a national wholesale brokerage. Before that, Amy led Business Development efforts for NORCAL Group’s Admitted and E&S business lines, managing teams across four regional offices nationwide. She initially entered the insurance field on the retail side, holding the position of Executive Vice President at a regional retail agency that specialized in healthcare liability insurance.

Amy’s remarkable journey in insurance, spanning over two decades, is marked by her commitment to servant leadership, her impressive track record of achieving growth and retention, and her dedication to mentoring high-performing collaborative teams. Her expertise in the medical professional liability sector has earned her the admiration of her peers, recognizing her as a visionary leader and expert in the field.

In her time off, Amy is passionate about outdoor activities, advocating for animal rights, and finds joy in traveling and reading.

Natalie Fanin is the Executive Vice President of Commercial Lines Service at Inszone Insurance Services. She currently leads a team of managers and is responsible for hiring, training, and empowering insurance professionals to demonstrate high accountability. Natalie started her insurance career in 2006, just days after her 18th birthday which ultimately developed her strong work ethic in the professional field. Prior to joining Inszone in November 2013, Natalie worked with a workers compensation wholesaler and a large insurance agency, holding a management role. Her experience in management, sales, service, and underwriting laid the foundation on how to be a successful insurance professional. Her relationship skills with policyholders, carrier partners and team members has led her to developing a team with a can-do attitude that goes above and beyond creating a great customer experience. Her ability to identify and educate on exposures has led the department in tremendous growth while holding high retention. Natalie continues to take initiative and is impactful in many areas on both the agency and carrier side while developing the next level of leaders that take pride and ownership in their work product.

On her time off, Natalie enjoys reading, hiking, and spending time with her son and really any other kiddos. She is dedicated to investing into the next generation which includes playing tag, roller skating/blading, playing games and teaching them new skills.

Norma Villafranca is a VP Los Angeles/Central California at Inszone Insurance Services. Her career in the insurance industry goes back to 2008. Before joining Inszone Insurance Services in 2016, she served as an Office Manager, quickly moving up to become District Manager and Area Project Manager for one of the largest personal lines agencies in the country. Norma is exceptionally well-respected, not only for her excellent customer service and high ethical standards but for being an honest, hardworking ally for her customers. The majority of her new clients are referral-based, being recommended by satisfied customers. She is never too busy to help and will do absolutely everything in her power to ensure a great experience.

Since starting at Inszone, she has been awarded some of the agency’s highest honors:

Inszone – Rookie of the Year for 2017

Inszone – Leadership Award for 2018

Inszone – Core Values Award for 2020

On her time off, she enjoys spending time outdoors, camping and hiking with her family.

Sara Evans is the Vice President for the Arizona region at Inszone Insurance Services, bringing over two decades of extensive experience in various sectors of the insurance industry. She attended the University of Nevada-Las Vegas, and her commitment to professional growth and excellence is marked by accolades such as the All-American Agent and JD Power Agent awards.

In her current role at Inszone, Sara plays a pivotal part in overseeing operations in the state of Arizona. She is dedicated to strategically recruiting, training, and motivating each team member to excel in their roles, with a keen emphasis on fostering strong customer relationships. Sara believes that a customer-centric approach is essential for the Arizona team to consistently deliver an exceptional experience to all clients.

In addition to her professional accomplishments, Sara places great importance on spending leisure time with her husband and two children.

Jennifer Turner is the VP Missouri at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in September 2021 after the merger with Summit Insurance Group. Jennifer is a graduate of Fort Hays State University and has earned designations from the National Alliance of Insurance Agents as a Certified Commercial Insurance Counselor (CIC) and Certified Risk Manager (CRM). Jennifer brings with her over 27 years of experience in personal and commercial risk management knowledge which allows her to help clients implement strong insurance programs for their individual needs. She enjoys training and mentoring insurance sales professionals as they develop deeper knowledge and lasting careers in the industry. One of Jennifer’s niche areas of expertise is the contractor trades and the many insurance requirements involved on large construction projects. She is always looking for ways to bring added value to her client’s insurance buying experience.

On her off time, Jennifer enjoys spending time with her family, traveling, and volunteering. She is a member of Rotary International and a local pet rescue program. She also helps her husband maintain their small acreage including their 4 dogs, 2 goats, and a few honeybee hives.

Bouachan Carey is the Vice President of Northern California Personal Lines at Inszone Insurance Services. An Insurance Veteran, Bouachan has over 15 years of experience in the Insurance Industry. She began her career as a personal insurance agent and quickly rose up the ranks to train and lead a variety of insurance teams. Her focus is on training and helping grow a team of insurance specialists that will be able to provide the best service possible to all customers. Bouachan joined Inszone in 2018, tasked with the growth and success of the personal insurance division, and she has not disappointed. Her experience has helped Inszone Insurance to expand into new markets and form stronger relationships with both customers and carriers.

On her time off, Bouachan enjoys spending every minute with her two wonderful kids.

Vito Migliore is a VP Employee Benefits Midwest Region at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in December 2021 after the merger with Lamb, Little & Co. Vito is a graduate of Valparaiso where he majored in accounting and business. He also earned his Chartered Life Underwriter (CLU) designation from The American College.

With over 30 years of insurance experience, he has helped grow the benefits department at Lamb, Little & Co to over $1.7 million in agency commission revenue. He also oversaw the agency’s accounting department and was a managing board member who was involved in the setting of the overall direction for the agency.

Vito has built long standing relationships with his customers and many of them have been with him for more than 20 years. To show how successful he’s been he received top sales recognition in his region when he worked at MetLife and Guardian. To credit his success, he uses a consultative approach when working with his customers to make sure that he is responsive to them no matter what their issue may be.

For over the past 20 years, Vito has also been active in youth sports, coaching hockey, and baseball, he is proud to share that additionally he has his Level 4 hockey coaching designation.

Vito has been married to his wife, Maureen for over 33 years, and they have three adult children that they are very proud of. In his off time, he enjoys spending time with his family, working out and playing hockey and golf.

Richard Choe is a Business Unit Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. Richard began his Insurance career in 1999 with a focus on commercial insurance. He brought a fierce determination to help business owners of all sizes protect their investments and quickly developed a large and very loyal client base. He understands that each situation is unique, and prides himself on the ability to develop a deep understanding of a business before creating custom solutions tailored to meet those individual needs.

Richard has always been interested in the constantly evolving insurance landscape and dedicates significant time to stay in tune with the market shifts. Critical knowledge in helping his clients navigate an ever-changing marketplace as well as meeting the dynamic needs of a growing business.

He joined Inszone in September 2020 after the acquisition of his previous company, Global Pacific Insurance Services.

In his spare time, Richard enjoys hiking, backpacking and spending time with his wonderful family.

Lauren Olson is a Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in May 2024 after the merger with Cascade Insurance Center. She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from Point Loma Nazarene University in San Diego, California. Early in her career, Lauren taught at an elementary school in a small village in Ghana, Africa. After marrying her husband Bo and having two children, she decided to return to her hometown of Bend to be closer to her family. It was there that Lauren discovered her passion for the insurance industry.

Lauren is dedicated to assisting her clients in navigating the complexities of the insurance world, helping them create comprehensive insurance portfolios. She believes that insurance is an essential component of a person’s financial portfolio and strives to make it easy to understand. Lauren has earned her Certified Insurance Counselor (CIC) certification from The National Alliance of Insurance Education and Research and serves on several insurance carrier committees, representing her clients’ interests. Lauren was also awarded the 2024 “Agent of the Year” by Professional Insurance Agents Western Alliance.

Committed to giving back to her community, Lauren has served on the board of the Family Access Network Foundation for many years, including the last two as the board chair.

In her free time, Lauren enjoys reading historical fiction novels while snuggling with her Australian Shepherd, Rocky.

Blake Devoy is a Senior Commercial Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in August 2023 after the merger with DeVoy Baker Insurance. Blake holds a bachelor’s degree in business administration from Missouri Western State University. With over 20 years of experience in the Insurance Industry, Blake brings a wealth of expertise.

Blake’s insurance journey began as a Licensed Insurance Producer in 2002. He then spent 5 years at Auto-Owners Insurance, working as a Claims Adjuster and Commercial Lines Underwriter. In 2012, he returned to his previous agency and progressively moved up the ranks, becoming an agency manager, producer, and eventually a principal in 2020.

Beyond his professional accomplishments, Blake is deeply involved in his community. He serves as the Vice President of the Brookfield R-3 School Board and is an active member of the North Central MO YMCA board. His leadership extends to his prior role as President of the Brookfield Area Chamber of Commerce and his current involvement with the Planning and Zoning Commission for the City of Brookfield.

Blake prides himself on his determined nature and ability to connect with others. In his time off, he enjoys spending quality time with his family, participating in his children’s extracurricular activities, and making meaningful contributions to his community.

Don Hudson is a Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in February 2024 after the merger with JHC Insurance Agency. He holds a Bachelor of Business Administration degree from Baylor University and is also a Certified Insurance Counselor. Don’s professional journey includes serving as an Executive Vice-President of Combined Agents of America, LLC, as well as holding positions such as Personal Lines Insurance Manager for Hilb, Rogal & Hamilton Company and serving on the Agents Council for Hochheim Prairie Insurance Company.

With over 24 years of agency ownership under his belt, Don brings a wealth of experience and expertise to his role. Beyond his professional endeavors, he is actively involved in his community, serving as a Deacon & Trustee at First Baptist Church of Victoria, TX, and as a Past Board Member of The Food Bank of the Golden Crescent. Additionally, Don is a Member of Northside Rotary in Victoria, TX, and has previously served as a Director of the TV Ministry at First Baptist Church.

In his free time, Don enjoys a variety of outdoor activities including hunting, fishing, golf, and skeet shooting. He also finds joy in spending quality time with his grandchildren and indulging in video games.

Hauke Hansen is a Commercial Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in August 2023 after the merger with Hawks View Insurance. Hauke has been a licensed agent in property, casualty, life, and health insurance since 2001. He also holds the designation of certified insurance counselor. His passion lies in assisting businesses and individuals with problem-solving, always focusing on their unique needs.

Throughout his career, Hauke has taken on various roles in the insurance industry. He has experience in working with specific carriers as well as in brokerage operations. His roles encompasses sales, service, management, and even business ownership. This diverse background allows Hauke to connect with business owners not only from an insurance and risk management standpoint but also from the perspective of real-world business operations.

Hauke values his team and is dedicated to improving their roles within the company. He is honored by the trust his staff has shown in his leadership and is also grateful for his nomination as the 2023 Mason County “Boss of the Year.”

Outside of work, Hauke is active in the community through volunteer events, particularly with organizations like Habitat for Humanity, Rotary, and the Chamber of Commerce. In addition, he has also taken on various roles, including serving as the President of his territory network chapter.

In his leisure time, he enjoys spending quality moments with his family and friends. He eagerly anticipates opportunities for travel, whether near or far, in search of unique experiences. Camping, hiking, grilling, cooking, and socializing are on top of his list of preferred activities. Occasionally, he engages in a round of golf, often enjoyed alongside his son Alec and his spouse of over two decades, Julie.

Justin Wood is a Senior Commercial Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in January 2024 after the merger with Checotah Insurance Agency. In 2016, fueled by a passion for entrepreneurship, Justin purchased an independent insurance agency, overseeing all aspects of the business. Within three years, strategic planning led to the agency’s expansion across multiple counties.

Recognized with the Distinguished Agent Award from 2017 to 2021 and earning the Commercial Lines Coverage Specialist (CLCS) Designation in 2017, Justin showcases determination and business acumen. With over a decade of training and development experience, he empowers others, previously serving as the Subject Matter Coordinator at Pasadena PVC.

As a Board Member of the Checotah Chamber of Commerce, Justin strengthens economic vitality and quality of life in Checotah. His dedication supports initiatives for commerce, job creation, and community growth.

In his time off, Justin’s adventurous spirit shines through his pilot’s license and outdoor hobbies. He enjoys time at the lake and hunting excursions with loved ones.

Kim Wood is a Senior Commercial Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in January 2024 after the merger with Checotah Insurance Agency. Kim began her insurance journey in 2016 when she and her husband acquired an agency in Oklahoma. Within three years, the agency expanded, including Wood Insurance Agency, spanning multiple counties.

Prior to her insurance career, Kim dedicated 18 years to educating young minds in elementary education, holding a Bachelor of Science from the University of Houston. Making a career change in 2016, she has since grown their agencies across the state of Oklahoma.

Kim proudly serves as a board member of the Stigler Chamber of Commerce, actively contributing to community growth. Known for her dedication to excellence, she brings a strong work ethic and compassionate heart to her roles.

In her free time, Kim enjoys creating lasting memories at the lake with her family and planning the perfect getaways through her passion for researching vacations.

Roy Sanfilippo is a Senior Personal Lines Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in July 2023 after the merger with Sanfilippo & Sons Insurance Services LLC. He attended San Jose City College, Mission College, and San Jose State on a partial scholarship for baseball, where Roy studied Business Management. During his junior year at San Jose State, Roy made the decision to leave and accelerate his entry into the family business with his father and two brothers. Prior to that, he gained valuable experience by working for an insurance company for two years.

Roy has been a member of the Sons of Sicily, Italian Heritage Foundation, and Holy Name Society of St. Christopher’s Church. His father’s words of wisdom, when his three sons joined the agency, remain ingrained in him: “Whether you have a $200K account or a $20.00 account, you treat your customers the same.” Over the years, Roy has always taken pride in building strong relationships with his clients and tending to their needs. He truly believes that this approach is the key to the family business’s success, which has spanned over 60 years.

In his leisure time, Roy enjoys fishing, golfing, playing pickleball, and following baseball. He also coached his kids in little league baseball and soccer.

Shane Butler is a Senior Commercial Insurance Specialist / Branch Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in September 2023 after the merger with Butler Insurance Services Inc. Shane is a US Navy Veteran, and Idaho native. Throughout his life in Idaho and 18-year insurance career, he has come to know many local families and developed relationships with businesses all over the state. These local relationships have helped him better understand the needs of an agency, and the community he proudly serves.

Shane is a very proud family man, father of 3 beautiful daughters, and enjoys time boating with his family and friends, traveling, skiing and playing golf. Shane has been married to his beautiful wife Stacy for over 20 years and cannot wait for their next exciting adventure together!

Rick Corbett is a Branch Manager as well as a Commercial Insurance & Risk Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. Rick joined the company in March 2023 after the merger with Corbett & Associates Insurance Agents & Brokers which he co-founded in 1986 and served as President & CEO. With years of experience in the insurance industry, Rick specializes in commercial property, property manager’s insurance programs, auto repair programs, and private client programs.

Throughout his career, Rick has actively participated in various advisory boards and producer councils. He was also part of the insurance advisory board for Assemblyman Tony Strickland, representing the California State Assembly 37th District from 1998 to 2004. Moreover, Rick played a crucial role in the formation of a notable insurance service, where he served as chairman for two years and as a board member for twelve years.

Rick earned his BA in interdisciplinary business from California State University, Northridge, and completed the Insurance & Risk Management Program offered by the university’s School of Business & Economics.

Aside from his work, Rick has been happily married to his wife Julie for over 3 decades, and together they raised three children and have four grandchildren. He actively supports community associations and youth sports programs, including coaching golf for the Ventura County Junior Golf Association, coaching football for the Thousand Oaks Titans junior football league, and volunteering as a booster for the Thousand Oaks Lancers football and band programs.

During his free time, Rick enjoys golfing, camping, surfing, skiing, and supporting his favorite football teams, the Seattle Seahawks and the Oregon Ducks.

Ann Pederson is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. Ann helps business owners with their insurance programs to make certain the have the affordable and comprehensive protection to fit their specific needs. She started in the insurance industry in 2016 after 15 years in the restaurant industry. She grew up in a small town and spent 14 years in the US Air Force National Guard which taught her the meaning of trust, integrity, accountability. Her degree in Financial Planning helps her to understand her clients’ financial needs as business owners and protect what they work hard for. Ann strives for excellence, and her mission is to deliver the best possible service to her clients.

Ann joined Inszone in November 2021 after the merger with her previous company, Stromsoe Insurance Agency.

On her time off, Ann enjoys participating on multiple Committees that focus on helping Veterans transitioning out of the military and Veteran business owners as well as spouses, camping and spending time with her three kids and fiancé, and visiting her hometown in Minnesota (in the summer).

Erika Roys is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. Erika is originally from Lima, Peru, where she attended Law School at UNIFE University. Erika began her professional career in the insurance industry in 2010 as an Insurance Representative for a reputable insurance agency in Pacific Grove, CA. She brings more than a decade of experience in both personal and commercial lines. Erika currently holds a Certification in Commercial Lines (CLIC) and a Workers’ Compensation Insurance Professional (WCIP) designation and is looking forward to expanding her education. She has been in management roles for almost a decade leading Commercial Lines Teams for well-known agencies. Erika has also directed the implementation of new procedures, software, and third-party services for her prior agencies to help improve their staff efficiency.

Erika is very passionate about insurance. She enjoys assisting her clients with risk analysis, providing the most appropriate coverages and best rates possible. As an established leader, Erika understands trust and support are fundamental factors to a successful team. Her continued focus is to mentor her team in their professional growth in Commercial Lines.

Erika loves music and taught herself to play the guitar at the age of 15. She enjoys road trips and vacations at mountain retreats with her husband and two fur-babies, Junior & Oscar, and visiting her family in her homeland, Peru.

Israel Sepulveda is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. An insurance veteran, he began his insurance career in 2005 with a focus on personal insurance. He switched his focus to commercial insurance when he joined Inszone in 2017. Utilizing a variety of skills honed throughout his many years of industry experience, Israel quickly grew a loyal customer base and has primarily focused on contractors and property risks. To this day he continues to impress with his hard work, consistency and care for each and every one of his customers. He is never too busy to help his clients! If you are looking to obtain or improve your business insurance, Israel will be a valuable asset to your process and planning.

Awards:

2018 Inszone’s Rookie of the Year

In his spare time, Israel enjoys playing sports and spending time with his family.

Josh Jackson is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in May 2023 after the merger with Jackson Insurance Solutions. Josh is a graduate of Hartford School of Insurance and has over 25 years of experience in the insurance industry, including over 15 years of managing and owning an independent insurance office. Josh was also appointed by the New Mexico Superintendent of Insurance to sit on their workers’ compensation dispute board, where he served for three years. Beyond his insurance expertise, Josh is a lead mentor for a youth group of 35 teenage boys and organizes monthly service projects in his community. These projects include working with food banks, community cleanups, individual help for the disabled, and visiting senior care centers, among other things. Josh takes pride in his honesty, intelligence, hardworking attitude, and his genuine care for others.

Josh is a proud father of three awesome little boys and a loving husband to his high school sweetheart. Josh is very involved in his church, and in his time off, he enjoys spending most of his time with his family. Josh loves spending time in the outdoors and is an avid fly fisherman. He also enjoys woodworking and makes furniture as a hobby.

Philip McClendon is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in March 2023 after the merger with Citizens General Insurance Brokers. At the time of joining Inszone, he brought over 20 years of experience as an entrepreneur in business, bringing a wealth of sales and management expertise to his role. Having owned his own business for many years, he is deeply committed to assisting small business owners in obtaining the right insurance coverage for their assets at the best possible value. As a service-disabled US Air Force veteran and devout Christian, Philip holds strong values of service and community involvement. His unwavering commitment to excellence, coupled with his passion for helping others, makes him a trusted and valued professional at Inszone Insurance Services.

In his time off, he enjoys spending quality time with his beloved wife, son, and daughters, often engaging in outdoor activities such as mountain biking, fishing, and boating.

Richard Park is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services. Richard brings with him over a decade of knowledge in banking, customer service, financial planning, and business experience.

In addition to his Property and Casualty License, he held a Series 6 and 63 and holds a Life and Variable Contracts License. Richard is skilled in developing long term relationships with clients that led him to becoming one of the top bankers in his region, and because he is determined, ambitious and has unquestionable work ethics, he knows his prior career will translate well into the world of insurance.

In his off time, he enjoys boxing, going to the shooting range, building rifles, hunting, and travelling the world. His goal is to eventually go to every country and sample every cuisine the world has to offer.

Weston Corbett is a Commercial Sales Team Manager at Inszone Insurance Services, joining the company in March 2023 after the merger with Corbett & Associates Insurance Agents & Brokers. He is a seasoned insurance professional with a decade of experience in personal and commercial lines insurance. He has consistently demonstrated a strong passion for helping clients safeguard their assets and achieve their financial goals. His dedication to his clients is evident in everything he does, and he takes great pride in his work. As he believes, “Hard work is the key to success in any profession. When you remain committed to your goals and put in the effort, anything is possible.” Weston’s exceptional work ethic and commitment to his clients have earned him a reputation as a trustworthy and dependable insurance professional. He looks forward to serving his community for many more years to come.

During his leisure time, Weston loves spending quality time with his lovely wife, Katherine, and their two amazing sons, Kayden and Easton. He is also an enthusiastic outdoorsman who enjoys fishing, golfing, and spending pleasant days at the lake.

Caralyn Torzewski is a Commercial Account Manager Team Lead at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in 2022 after the merger with Proctor Insurance Group. She started her adventure in the Insurance Industry in April 2000 in a small family-owned and operated agency. She has built up her knowledge and expertise in all fields and thrives in the Commercial Lines sector. She strives to provide the best service to all our clients.

“I enjoy learning about a client and their insurance needs and educating them about the risks and exposures they have, personally and professionally,” says Caralyn. While actively working, she started her college education to be an elementary school teacher. Within the first year of being in the insurance industry, she felt it was her calling to go into business. Although she’s not teaching little ones, she is teaching and educating adults to help them understand why the need for insurance is so important.

She has built a successful Hotel/Motel book of business and has broken barriers when it comes to women in this industry being recognized as an equal. She is known for her knowledge, skill, and ability to provide exceptional service. She earned her Associates Degree in Business from Lone Star College in 2010. She also obtained designations as a Certified Insurance Service Representative through the National Alliance in 2007 as well as a Certified Account Manager through the Independent Insurance Agents in 2015. She continues to learn and educate herself so that she can be the best agent and representative in the Insurance industry. She is a quick learner, detailed, determined, and strives for excellence in everything that she puts her mind to.

Outside of work, Caralyn loves watching the sun rise/set, watching the clouds, gazing at stars, doing arts and crafts, checking out new craft breweries, cooking, and doing fun activities like bowling, fishing, and going on nature walks. She would consider herself a go-getter and has an adventurous spirit. She has a passion for photography and will snap a picture of everything because she recognizes the beauty and significance of capturing moments in time. She loves spending time with her family and friends. She is a proud auntie of two beautiful nieces, Katelyn and Harper. She also loves spending time with her incredible boyfriend, Adam, 3 pups – Lulu, Leo, and Moo, and 1 cat – Fendi.

Katelyn Haniotes is a Commercial Account Manager Team Lead at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in December 2021 after the merger with Desert Mountain Insurance Services, Inc. Katelyn takes pride in providing quality customer service to her clients. She graduated with her bachelor’s degree in Christian Studies with an emphasis in Youth Ministry from Grand Canyon University in December 2019. She is dedicated to helping others and has taken insurance as her route to fulfill that passion.

She has taken her prior experience as a Manager at Dutch Brothers Coffee to provide her current clients with quality products in a timely manner. Her goal as an insurance agent is to help her clients find the best coverage while making the experience as easy and enjoyable for them as possible.

During her off time, Katelyn enjoys spending time outdoors such as hiking or camping, spending quality time with her close companions, and has recently taken up line dancing as a hobby.

Lois Owen is a Commercial Lines Account Manager Team Lead at Inszone Insurance Services, joining Inszone in June 2023. Her insurance journey began in 1997 when she started as a file clerk for a small insurance agency in Joliet, IL. Intrigued by the insurance industry, she obtained her license in 2003 and started selling personal and commercial lines insurance. It was in 2005 that she discovered her passion for hospitality insurance, becoming an expert in the field. Over the past 20 years, Lois has dedicated herself to helping, training, and working alongside other agents and employees in the commercial insurance industry.

Lois Owen is highly respected for her commitment to excellent customer service and adherence to ethical standards. She firmly believes that customer satisfaction is the key to loyalty, as customers will remain with a company where they are well-treated.
